{"text": "2005", "bbox": [955.3, 916.6, 992.9, 935.4]}, {"text": "Health care cost trend rate assumed for next year", "bbox": [247.4, 944.7, 619.4, 963.5]}, {"text": "9.0%", "bbox": [746.3, 944.7, 785.4, 963.5]}, {"text": "10.0%", "bbox": [849.5, 944.7, 898.0, 963.5]}, {"text": "10.0%", "bbox": [961.6, 944.7, 1010.2, 963.5]}, {"text": "Rate to which the cost trend rate is assumed to decline", "bbox": [247.4, 971.9, 659.6, 990.6]}, {"text": "(the ultimate trend rate)", "bbox": [277.0, 998.9, 459.4, 1017.6]}, {"text": "5.0%", "bbox": [745.8, 998.9, 784.9, 1017.6]}, {"text": "5.0%", "bbox": [858.3, 998.9, 897.5, 1017.6]}, {"text": "5.0%", "bbox": [970.5, 998.9, 1009.6, 1017.6]}, {"text": "Year that the rate reached the ultimate trend rate", "bbox": [247.4, 1026.0, 614.7, 1044.8]}, {"text": "2015", "bbox": [743.1, 1026.0, 780.7, 1044.8]}, {"text": "2011", "bbox": [852.0, 1026.0, 889.5, 1044.8]}, {"text": "2008", "bbox": [965.4, 1026.0, 1003.0, 1044.8]}, {"text": "Assumed long-term rates of return on plan assets, discount rates for estimating benefit obligations, and", "bbox": [215.8, 1081.4, 1078.1, 1102.3]}, {"text": "rates of compensation increases vary for the different plans according to the local economic conditions.  The", "bbox": [140.7, 1108.5, 1050.7, 1129.4]}, {"text": "weighted average assumptions for the Nigerian, Indian, and Indonesian plans are not included in the above tables as", "bbox": [140.7, 1135.7, 1112.4, 1156.5]}, {"text": "the plans were immaterial.  The discount rates were determined based on the prevailing market rate of a portfolio of", "bbox": [140.7, 1162.7, 1111.3, 1183.5]}, {"text": "high-quality debt instruments with maturities matching the expected timing of the payment of the benefit", "bbox": [140.7, 1189.8, 1021.6, 1210.7]}, {"text": "obligations.  For our United Kingdom pension plan, which constitutes 76% of our international pension plans’", "bbox": [140.7, 1216.9, 1064.8, 1237.8]}, {"text": "projected benefit obligation, the discount rate increased from 5.0% at September 30, 2006 to 5.7% at September 30,", "bbox": [140.7, 1243.9, 1112.1, 1264.8]}, {"text": "2007.", "bbox": [140.7, 1271.0, 192.9, 1291.9]}, {"text": "The overall expected long-term rate of return on assets was determined based upon an evaluation of our", "bbox": [215.8, 1298.2, 1086.2, 1319.1]}, {"text": "plan assets, historical trends, and experience, taking into account current and expected market conditions.", "bbox": [140.7, 1325.2, 1025.0, 1346.1]}, {"text": "Our investment strategy varies by country depending on the circumstances of the underlying plan.", "bbox": [215.8, 1352.4, 1043.9, 1373.3]}, {"text": "Typically, less mature plan benefit obligations are funded by using more equity securities, as they are expected to", "bbox": [140.7, 1379.5, 1092.7, 1400.4]}, {"text": "achieve long-term growth while exceeding inflation.  More mature plan benefit obligations are funded using more", "bbox": [140.7, 1406.5, 1097.0, 1427.4]}, {"text": "fixed income securities, as they are expected to produce current income with limited volatility.  Risk management", "bbox": [140.7, 1433.6, 1095.2, 1454.5]}, {"text": "practices include the use of multiple asset classes and investment managers within each.", "bbox": [140.7, 1460.7, 880.6, 1481.6]}]}